<%# Claimable payout, hidden until the settlement controller fills it. This is the payee's money, so it leads
    with the amount, keeps the token (data) in mono, and gives one clear claim instruction. %>
<div data-settlement-target="payout" class="mt-4 hidden rounded-xl border border-copper-dim/40 bg-copper/5 p-4">
	<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
		<span class="grid size-9 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-lg border border-copper-dim/40 bg-canvas text-copper">
			<i class="hgi-stroke hgi-coins-01 text-lg" aria-hidden="true"></i>
		</span>

		<div class="min-w-0 flex-1">
			<p class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">Payout ready: <span data-settlement-target="payoutAmount" class="font-mono">0</span> sat</p>
			<p class="mt-0.5 text-xs leading-relaxed text-ink-secondary">
				Your funds are this Cashu token. Copy it into any Cashu wallet to claim them, and keep it safe: the token is the money.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-1 text-xs leading-relaxed text-ink-faint">
				If the mint charges a redeem fee, this amount is already net of it. Cashing out to Lightning may cost a small mint fee too.
			</p>

			<div class="mt-3 flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border bg-inset px-3 py-2">
				<textarea data-settlement-target="payoutToken" readonly rows="2" aria-label="Your Cashu payout token"
					class="min-w-0 flex-1 resize-none bg-transparent font-mono text-xs text-ink-secondary focus:outline-none"></textarea>
				<button type="button" data-action="settlement#copyPayout"
					class="shrink-0 self-start rounded-md px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-copper transition-colors hover:bg-surface focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-copper-bright">Copy</button>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
